-1.title: Heartthrobs
-1.plot: Justin Bieber invites us along to give a helping hand to a family in need, we find out what Cody Simpson looks for when it comes to love, and MKTO plays an intimate fan concert at the Young Hollywood studio. Plus, exclusive interviews and performances by MKTO, Olly Murs, and Matt Hunter!

1.title: Cool Kids
1.plot: Ellie Goulding shares the ups and downs of being on tour, Foster the People breaks down their method to making music, Neon Trees tell us how they stand apart from the crowd, and Florence Welch of Florence + the Machine talks about the art of naming her albums. Plus, exclusive interviews with Passion Pit, Of Monsters and Men, and The Neighbourhood!

2.title: Divas
2.plot: Superstar Alicia Keys tells us the importance of passion in her work, Kelly Rowland shares her advice for breaking into the music world, Emeli Sandé talks making music history, and Becky G. tells us what it's like working with top talent in the industry. Plus, exclusive performances and interviews from Tori Kelly, Cimorelli, and the Wonder Girls!

4.title: Kings of EDM
4.plot: World-renowned DJ David Guetta breaks down the definition of pop music, Martin Solveig shares what it's like working with top talent, and Skrillex talks style and comfort at the Grammys. Plus, exclusive interviews with Steve Aoki, Paul Oakenfold, and DJ Skeet Skeet!

5.title: Country Faves
5.plot: Country sweetheart Taylor Swift reveals what it takes to make chart-topping hits. Carrie Underwood shows us a glimpse into her tour life. Sibling trio The Band Perry gets protective in the Young Hollywood Studio, and Blake Shelton explains what makes him a real countryman. Plus, exclusive interviews with Florida Georgia Line, Lady Antebellum, and Little Big Town.

6.title: One of a Kind Characters
6.plot: Kesha's iconic fashion is explained, and LMFAO gives us an exclusive tour of their home.

8.title: Beat Poetry
8.plot: Rap legend Ice Cube talks transitioning from music to movies, T.I lays down some very important rules, Flo Rida reveals the secret to his success, and Ice-T explains the art to rap music. Plus, exclusive interviews from Jay Sean, Big Boi, and Tinie Tempah!

9.title: Soulful Sounds
9.plot: The Fray reveals where they pull their musical inspiration from, Colbie Caillat talks about how she connects with her fans through her music, and Gavin DeGraw shares his secret to always staying relevant in the music world. Plus, exclusive interviews and performances from G. Love, Brandon and Leah, and Phillip Phillips.

10.title: Making of a Music Video
10.plot: Lady Gaga tells us how she plans to change the world through her music, hip-hop artist The Game talks collaborating on set with some of Hollywood's biggest talent, and pop group Karmin shows us some of their music video dance moves. Plus, exclusive interviews with OK Go, Far East Movement, and Parachute!

11.title: The Recording Studio
11.plot: Producer J.R. Rotem talks about collaborating with music's top artists, Sean Kingston gives us a private tour of his studio, and Jesse McCartney shares what inspires him to write chart-topping hits. Plus, exclusive interviews from Alex Da Kid and RedOne!

12.title: Going on Tour
12.plot: Lady Gaga shares some favorite fan experiences while on the road, OneRepublic tells us what going on tour means to them, and Portugal The Man shares the challenges they faced while traveling the world. Plus, exclusive interviews with Owl City, Dashboard Confessional, Cobra Starship, and Kodaline!

13.title: Backstage Pass
13.plot: Pop Superstar Demi Lovato shares some words of wisdom, we find out who the true inspiration behind Jason Derulo's work is, and 30 Seconds to Mars shares one of their most memorable tour memories. Plus, exclusive interviews with Bastille, Temper Trap, The Ceremonies, and Black Veil Brides.

imdb.plot outline: Music junkies rejoice as we interview today's most talked about musicians. The episodes include exclusive acoustic performances, music festivals, rides on tour buses, heartthrobs and recording sessions. Find out what amps up the talented faces behind the songs we love.
